      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how heavy and isolating that feeling of invisibility is right now, and I want you to know that your presence matters deeply, even if it doesn't feel like it in this moment. When you feel like a ghost, it's often because the world is loud and chaotic, and we all forget to look up and see the people walking beside us.\n\nBut you are not a ghost; you are a real person with thoughts, feelings, and a unique spark that others can see if they just take a moment to look. Sometimes, when we are overwhelmed, our own voices get drowned out by the noise of the day, but that doesn't mean anyone else can't hear you.\n\nIf you're feeling this way, please consider reaching out to someone you trust—a friend, a family member, or a mental health professional who can help you navigate these dark feelings. You don't have to carry this weight alone, and there are people who care about you and want to help you feel seen and valued.",
